> Should it be called `entourageProd`? Uniformity is the filter, not its base sets. @PatrickMassot

@urkud : I had the same exchange with Sébastien Gouëzel on another file a couple of weeks ago. The decision was to use "entourage" there, and it makes the file clearer.

I've implemented this change (UniformityProd -> entourageProd).

```suggestion
def uniformityProd (u : Set (α × α)) (v : Set (β × β)) : Set ((α × β) × α × β) :=
```

```suggestion
    {((a₁, b₁), (a₂, b₂)) | (a₁, a₂) ∈ u ∧ (b₁, b₂) ∈ v}
```

```suggestion
  {((a₁, b₁),(a₂, b₂)) | (a₁, a₂) ∈ u ∧ (b₁, b₂) ∈ v}
```

